topics.body:
I'm going to spend five more minutes here(finishing dinner), but personally I think asian immigration will probably massively increase in the next couple years personally.

Why?
1)Japan's economy is sinking due to several factors but mainly decrease in population and they're having to deal with constant economic stagnation.
2)Mainland China is a terrible place to live.(22% of asian immigrants are from china)
3)A lot of the people are coming to the USA cause their home country either is in severe economic stagnation.
There's lots of other driving factors, but those are the main issues.  Personally I think China should totally set up a deal with the USA to let people immigrate to the USA cause that would make a lot of things easier.
